    <node id="1. Lax discipline and investigation on the tramp freighter: The skipper of the freighter was on his last flight before retirement, and the crew's discipline was lax. Additionally, investigation of new personnel was even more relaxed, which allowed Ben to successfully stow away on the ship.&#10;&#10;2. Help from friends: Although not explicitly mentioned, it is implied that Ben and Jake had friends who helped them escape from Hoover City and provided them with a hiding place, a small desert-taxi, and a pass to leave the city. These friends were likely part of the group of spacemen that Jake was associated with, who operate beyond Mars and have established a base on an asteroid.&#10;&#10;3. Ben's resourcefulness: Ben demonstrated resourcefulness by finding a way to escape Earth and make his way to Venus. He lied about having been in Hoover City before, and he managed to get rid of his uniform and change his name to avoid detection.&#10;&#10;4. Luck: Ben also had some luck on his side, as he was able to find a tramp freighter whose skipper was on his last flight before retirement. This allowed him to blend in with the crew more easily and avoid detection." />
