    <edge source="&#10; She left the room.&#10; &#10; &#10;&#10; &#10; He sank into the softness of his bed. As he turned over on his side, his gaze fell upon an object on a bureau in a far corner of the room.&#10; &#10; He sat straight up, his chest heaving.&#10; &#10; The object was a tri-dimensional photo of a rock-faced man in a merchant spaceman's uniform. He was a giant of a man with a neatly trimmed red beard !&#10; &#10; Ben stared at the photo for a long time. At length, he slipped into restless sleep. Images of faces and echoes of words spun through his brain.&#10; &#10; The dead man returned to him. Bloodied lips cursed at him. Glassy eyes accused him. Somewhere were two lost children crying in the night.&#10; &#10; And towering above him was a red-bearded man whose great hands reached down and beckoned to him. Ben crawled through the night on hands and knees, his legs numb and useless. The crying of the children was a chilling wail in his ears.&#10; &#10; His head rose and turned to the red-bearded man. His pleading voice screamed out to him in a thick, harsh cackle. Yet even as" target="The &quot;dead man&quot; that Ben is trying to find and escape from is named Cobb, a stout and flabby man of about forty who hated spacemen. Ben is haunted by Cobb's image, which appears as a pop-eyed mask of surprise or a frozen face with gaping mouth and trickling blood. Ben wants to forget a living man like Cobb, but his death has made him an invisible Siamese twin to Ben.&#10;&#10;Ben needs to find the man with the red beard to escape from Cobb because he believes that this giant can help him. The story does not provide explicit details about their connection, but it is possible that the red-bearded man is a powerful figure who can protect Ben from Cobb or help him deal with his past as a junior astrogation officer and his current status as a fugitive charged with second degree murder and escape.&#10;&#10;It is also worth noting that the red-bearded man may have some connection to Jake, the girl who escaped with Ben from the Inn in Hoover City on Venus. The story mentions that Ben sees a tri-dimensional photo of a rock-faced man in a merchant spaceman's uniform with a neatly trimmed red beard in his room on Venus, and that this image haunts him in his sleep. It is possible that the red-bearded man is Jake's father or another member of her group of spacemen who operate beyond Mars and have established a base on an asteroid.">
