e at the time of the fight, which suggests that he was already on the run from the law and had likely experienced fear and stress related to his legal situation. Therefore, it is possible that these existing fears and anxieties contributed to his terror after striking Cobb and prompted him to flee the scene.&#10;&#10;In summary, Ben's terror after hitting Cobb seems to be a complex emotional response triggered by a combination of factors, including shock, guilt, fear of punishment, and anxiety related to his existing legal situation as a fugitive.">
