    <edge source="1. The asteroid miners plan to move their operations further into the frontier if there is a crackdown or when Space Corps ships officially reach the asteroids. They have already established a new base on an asteroid, beyond the reach of Earth's laws and society.&#10;2. The asteroid miners are able to continue their operations despite objections from authorities because they provide necessary transportation of cargo and supplies to frontier ports like Hoover City. They also have friends planted in the Interplanetary Bureau of Investigation (I.B.I.), making it difficult for the authorities to ignore them.&#10;3. The asteroid miners consist of about a thousand individuals with a dozen ships, half of whom are wanted by the I.B.I., while the others are physical or psycho rejects who cannot return to Earth even if they wanted to. They have formed their own community and have established a base on an asteroid where they can operate freely.&#10;4. The red-bearded man that Ben meets could potentially be a member of the asteroid miners' group, who may help Ben deal with his past as a junior astrogation officer and his current status as a fugitive charged with second degree murder and escape." target="1. The renegade spacemen operating from the Solar System's frontiers are a group of misfits and rejectees from the clearing houses on Earth. They consist of about a thousand individuals with a dozen ships, half of whom are wanted by the Interplanetary Bureau of Investigation (I.B.I.), while the others are physical or psycho rejects who cannot return to Earth even if they wanted to.&#10;2. Their purpose is to operate freely and make an honest living by transporting cargo and supplies to frontier ports like Hoover City, beyond the reach of Earth's laws and society. They have established a base on an asteroid and are accepted as a necessary part of life in the frontier ports despite their outlaw status.&#10;3. The renegade spacemen are not outlaws in the traditional sense, but rather individuals who cannot return to Earth and have formed their own community in the frontiers. They provide necessary transportation of cargo and supplies to the frontier ports, making it difficult for authorities to ignore them despite objections from some officials.">
